4.64/5  rDev +0.4%look: 4 | smell: 5 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.75Have had a few of these by now. August 2016 release.
A- Absurdly cloudy pale golden body like someone dissolved cereal into a beer pours from the tallboy into a tulip glass. A thick, creamy white head forms to about a finger high with decent retention. A medium ring drops a fair amount of webs and sheets of lacing. Truly milky and cloudy.
S- Despite having a massive amount of the pungent IPAs of today, this aroma is right up there at the top as far as pungency goes and it seems to have developed in the can as the juiciness is brighter and clearer than right at release time.  Tropical and citrus fruit nectar with plenty of melon, cantaloupe, oranges, grapefruit, pineapple, peach and tangerine. Rather dank as well.
T- For my palate the brew shifts quite a bit from the aroma to more of a sharp citrus and resinous brew with the tropical elements still mostly intact.  The taste opens up with bitter ruby red grapefruit, oranges, tangerine and clementine with hints of resinous pine, mango, pineapple, melon and dank herbs. A touch of raw cereal grains beneath the hop barrage.
MF- Fairly thick for the style and ABV with a slickness and a creamy texture. Very high end carbonation produces the necessary force to drive out those delicate hop tones. Finishes with an edgy high end bitterness.
Another amazing hoppy brew from Trillium. Perhaps in the top 5 beer aromas I have ever experienced with a taste that follows it up doing justice. Expect a truly pungent mix of citrus and tropical and infinite smoothness. 1,525 characterscbutova, Sep 30, 2016
