4.98/5  rDev +7.8%look: 5 | smell: 5 | taste: 5 | feel: 4.75 |  overall: 58/17/16 dated can poured into the special release " Headroom Stemmed / teku-ish"
Glass. 
The appearance / opacity is a couple notches above then norm for trillium. This is Tropicana OJ, seriously. Totally murky, and thick looking. Aggressive pour left a one finger off white head with nice large bubbles mixed with nice tight bubbles that fade within 30 seconds to a razor thin cap. 
Aroma is OFF THE HINGES GOOD ! It's an orgy of tropical fruits, citrus, some herbaceous green dankness that just don't quit! One second I get a heavy wave of oranges , then grapefruit, then another sniff is all pinnapple, then heavy dank hop oils. Nuts I tell ya. 
Taste basically follows suit. The first can I had on the night of the release ( sat 8/27 ) was still a bit green and " hot ".  The overwhelming amount of hops led to this crazy hoppy bite on the palate that just goes to show the obsurd amount of hops added. First is the Slighty prickly hops then all the usual citrus and tropical goodness. And finishes with a touch more of the slightly bitter spice, but leaves fairly quick. Also has that tooth enamel stripping feel that signals, assload of dry hopping !!
This does remind me a little of DDH Congress. 
The feel is medium body with medium minus carbonation. I wouldn't say creamy, but not thin. Nice feel. 
Overall, the hype is worth it to me. Some may say not so much. It's a huge double IPA worthy of seeking out.  The roller coaster ride of aroma and taste is worth the price of admission.  If you like the best of Trills other DDH Varients, then this should be an easy A+ 
7lbs of hops per bbl is bloody foolish, but oh so worth it  
Cheers ! 1,653 charactersSteve_Tkachuk, Sep 04, 2016
