Pours completely opaque turbid bright golden yellow with a frothy  white foam head. Smells super dank and green with earthy herbal grass, slight oniony cilantro, resinous pine sap, with citrusy tropical fruit notes of mango, melons, peach, guava, passionfruit, orange, and grapefruit. Tastes so juicy with tropical mango, caramelized peach, orange, grapefruit, passionfruit, guava, melon, slight oniony cilantro, sticky pine sap, with dank earthy herbal grass and resinous pine. Feels medium-full bodied, slick and creamy with moderate low carbonation. Overall a really great, super hoppy DIPA. 621 charactersStoutElk_92, Aug 28, 2016
4.54/5  rDev -1.7%look: 4.75 | smell: 5 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 3.5 |  overall: 4.5L - striking. Cracked the can and gazed inside. OJ here we go. Wow, pours a swampy murky turbid pale orange. Almost has a bit of a brownish yeasty hue to it. Reminds me of those frozen orange juice pops we used to make as kids. 
S - big yeasty aroma from the moment I opened the can. Candied orange up front that quickly turns to a deep resonating pine. Pineapples and a thick juicy humid tropical environment. There is so much pithy bitter orange. Might be one of the best-smelling beers I've come across. 
T - ripe citrus and Galaxy hops. Spicy, peppery hops clash with the candied tangerine. A fizzling bitterness works its way into the equation brought to life by a flavor experience quite similar to chewing on an orange peel. Rindy bitterness. This ain't just orange juice, it's the kind of OJ that you messily squeeze yourself from several slices of fresh-cut oranges, half of it making its way into your glass, and the other half on the table. End result is a few tablespoons of the rawest, most natural orange juice you've ever had. 
F - everybody talks about how creamy this is, but I actually got a bit of an airy, over carbonated vibe. Lots of these great DIPAs have the velvet mouthfeel that slicks its way between through your teeth and over your tongue, but when I try to do that here, it fluffs up a bit. Almost like the bubbles separate from the liquid and the first half of the sip is cream, but the second is mostly air. Swallowing lots of foam on the finish. Burps incoming!
O - Damn good beer, just not sure it lives up to the hype. Mouthfeel is off and makes it hard to enjoy this beer too much! Perhaps it just needs a few days in the can. Will report back later with my findings!
UPDATE 9/12/16: mouthfeel has simmered down a bit, but still foams up a bit in the swallow. Got one can left and am probably gonna hang onto it for a while to see what happens! 1,885 charactersagreenman19, Aug 28, 2016
