Pours a decent but smaller fizzy foamy 1/2 finger head that fades semi quickly, little lacing, murky milk shake creamy orange color.
Nose mixed, tons of juicy citrus orange cream tangerine, an interesting tropical citrus, little fruity bubblegum, hint of pine, mango sherbet, faint creamy malt.
Taste brings more citrus, big creamy orange juice, tangerine, a little grapefruit and more citrus tropical fruit, hint of mango sherbet, papaya, fair musty tropical fruit, touch of dankness and pine, a spicy chewy hop comes through later, little grassy earthy, and mild sweet malt. Finish is drier slight sweetness, fair bitterness, more chewy spicy earthy grassy hop, little orange rind and musty tropical notes, big spiciness late.
Mouth is med to thicker bod, fair creamy and rich almost like I'm chewing on it, decent carb, booze hidden well.
Overall not bad, wish the carbonation and head were better, malt profile and hidden booze were nice, hops were ok, although I expected a lot more tropical fruit and more pop from the hops, thankfully the mosaic wasn't an onion pine sap bomb. 1,141 charactersjlindros, Aug 28, 2016
